HEADWORD: midwestern
<hw>midwestern</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <def>Of or pertaining to the Midwest
region of the U. S., generally including Ohio; Indiana; Illinois; Iowa;
Missouri; Kansas; Nebraska; and sometimes Michigan; Wisconsin;
Minnesota; <as>as, a <ex>midwestern</ex> city; <ex>midwestern</ex>
accent</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
